    <string name="help_text_about">
        <p>Dog Seeker created by Karl Stewart for CMPT 276:\n
            <a href="https://opencoursehub.cs.sfu.ca/jackt/grav-cms/cmpt276-2/home">Course Homepage</a>\n</p>\n
        <b>INTERPOL PET</b> has called you in for \"one last mission\".\n
        <b>You must pet every dog.</b>\n
        <p>You take a department issued <b>PET</b> energy scanner, plastics faded with time, from your desk\.\.\.</p>\n
        <p>How does this thing work again?\n\n</p>
        <b>Scanning for dogs:</b>\n
        Each level has a set amount of hidden dogs.\n
        <p>1. Tap a cell to reveal any hidden dogs!\n</p>
        <p>2. If the cell doesn\'t have a hidden dog, the <b>PET</b> scanner will send out a dog radar pulse, updating the cell with the number of dogs in that cell\'s row and column.\n</p>
        <b>Pet all dogs with as few PET scans as possible.</b>
    </string>
